 <p style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">
  The sign for "people"
  <font face="Arial">
   is done three or more different ways.
   <br/>
   (Pity the poor unsuspecting ASL student--especially those taking a class from 
	a "my way is the
   <i>
    right
   </i>
   way" type of instructor).
  </font>
  <font face="Arial">
   <hr align="left" color="#000000" size="1"/>
  </font>
  <p style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">
   <font face="Arial">
    <br/>
    I personally use
    <b>
     forward
    </b>
    alternating rotational movement (as if 
	pedaling a bicycle forward).
    <br/>
    Many of my friends and associates also use a forward rotational movement.
    <br/>
    Some of my friends and associates use a
    <i>
     backward
    </i>
    rotational movement.
    <br/>
    A few use an up and down alternating movement.
   </font>
